Great food and even better service. Had the pizza which was great. Light and airy dough, not too much cheese or sauce. Large pie was a Sicilian and plentiful. Buffalo wings and calamari were delicious. Shrimp parm and baked penne were great, too. We’ll be back.

Ok. Not the best. My pasta was swimming in water. Sauce thin. Portions small. Waiter rude. Too expensive.

This is a little Italian gem located next to burgerfi. Second time coming here with family group over 8 people. The food is delicious. I got the tagliatelle Maria with grilled chicken (fresh pasta made daily).They cut the chicken up and mixed it with the pasta which was amazing compared to just putting sliced grilled chicken on top. The sweet and spicy calamari is different and delicious. Their standard grandma style pizza is very good as well. The setting is very a comfy NYC Italian vibe. The service is top notch as well. Courteous and attentive staff that suites the quality of food provided. Great date spot or family dinner. They also have more items on the menu than the website menu shows. Definitely will be coming back.

Very good service, good ambiance and attentive staff. They just need to work on the food. The rice balls taste good, but they should warm them up better, the cheese inside was very cold. If you don't offer fresh cooked food, at least learn to warm them up better. The calamari was overcooked and dry. The eggplant parmesan was tasty but the pasta was dry.

Nice little neighborhood joint with nice decoration and very good food. I had one of the specials of which I can not exactly recall the name. It was however with whole wheat pasta, spinach and homemade mozzarella which was very good. This is quite an accomplishment since homemade whole wheat pasta is difficult to make and certainly to make it pleasant which eat which it was. My wife had bucatini amatriciana which actually had a kick to it which was a very pleasant surprise. In all, for a little less than 60 dollars for an appetizer and 2 entrees with sodas, it was a very nice and pleasant experience and we will be back. The only single negative remark I can make is the reader over zealous waiter. He took plates away when we had barely finished or even when there was still a piece is bread left on it to scoop up some sauce.
No  matter what you order  you never disappointed.

Favourite dish was the meatballs and ricotta. The grandma pizzas were just OK in my opinion. They also do their own noodles. And the beef noodles dish was pretty good. I didn't have the chicken parm myself but I was told it was good. I wound go back just for the meatballs and the beef in noodles.

I'm just mad I paid cash instead of using a card because I would have definitely disputed the charges. I didn't eat one bite the entire thing went in the trash. Food is super fresh and made with REAL ingredients to create delectable Italian favorites which arrive at your table hot and with a smile.  The pesto sauce is perfection and the salad is simply delicious.  The staff is super, courteous and on point to please.  The prices are just right and the portions are sizable enough to take some home if you can resist eating all of it there.  The ambiance is easy and comfortable begging you to have some cappuccino and desert.  I will absolutely return with my friends.  A new found favorite.
